cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MM

This paper discusses the design of MAC protocols for WiFi networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of game theory to analyze the behavior of nodes in the network suggests that it could also be classified under the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT). The proposal of using the Access Point as an arbitrator for improving network performance suggests that it could also be classified under the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY). The evaluation of DCF extensions for practical implementation suggests that it could also be classified under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM).
